{"parse":{"title":"Red Ladder Theatre Company","pageid":28179813,"revid":846829745,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Red Ladder Theatre Company</b> is a national touring theatre company, funded by the <a href=\"/wiki/Arts_Council_England\" title=\"Arts Council England\">Arts Council England</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Leeds\" title=\"Leeds\">Leeds</a> City Council. It is based at the Yorkshire Dance Centre, Leeds.\n</p><p>The company was founded in London in 1968, during the Vietnam War, as a radical socialist theatre known as <i>agitprop</i>. The company moved to Leeds in the 1970s and is still based in the city. During the 1980s, the company changed its co-operative structure to a hierarchy and became a company that specialised in targeted work for youth audiences.\n</p><p>Red Ladder also hosted the <b>Asian Theatre School</b>, later Freedom Studios,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> preparing productions including the play <i>Silent Cry</i> by Madani Younis\npresented at the <a href=\"/wiki/Theatre_Royal,_York\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Theatre Royal, York\">Theatre Royal, York</a> (2004).<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2011, it ran a play called <i>Promised Land</i>, an adaptation of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Anthony_Clavane&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Anthony Clavane (page does not exist)\">Anthony Clavane</a>'s book about Leeds United.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SYT_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SYT-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Today the company:\n</p>\n<ul><li>tours nationally</li>\n<li>produces performance for the Annual Emerge Festival<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (March 2012)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Garforth_Arts_Festival\" title=\"Garforth Arts Festival\">Garforth Arts Festival</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-YEP_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-YEP-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Runs the Red Grit, Actor Training programme</li></ul>\n<p>Red Ladder's Arts Council funding will cease from April 2015.  In response to a fundraising campaign to save the company, author David Peace has donated the theatre rights to his novel <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Damned_Utd\" title=\"The Damned Utd\">The Damned Utd</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Red_Ladder_Theatre_Company&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Twentieth-Century British Theatre: Industry, Art and Empire - Page 267 1139502131 Claire Cochrane - 2011 \"... was part of the trajectory that would culminate in 2002 with the setting up of the British Asian-led Asian Theatre School.\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Liz Tomlin  British Theatre Companies: 1995-2014: Mind the Gap, Kneehigh ... 1408177307 - 2015 \"... groups of young people supported by Peshkar Productions in Oldham and the Asian Theatre School (later Freedom Studios), under the auspices of Red Ladder in Bradford.\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.britishtheatreguide.info/reviews/silentcry-rev\">Silent Cry review</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SYT-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-SYT_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.southyorkshiretimes.co.uk/lifestyle/actors-wanted-to-star-in-new-leeds-united-drama-1-4375829\">\"Actors wanted to star in new Leeds United drama\"</a>. <i>South Yorkshire Times</i>. 23 March 2012<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">23 March</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=South+Yorkshire+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Actors+wanted+to+star+in+new+Leeds+United+drama&amp;rft.date=2012-03-23&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.southyorkshiretimes.co.uk%2Flifestyle%2Factors-wanted-to-star-in-new-leeds-united-drama-1-4375829&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARed+Ladder+Theatre+Company\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-YEP-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-YEP_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Robinson, Paul (5 March 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/news/latest-news/top-stories/east-leeds-focus-on-garforth-arts-festival-1-4311196\">\"East Leeds: Focus on Garforth Arts Festival\"</a>. <i>Yorkshire Evening Post</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">23 March</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3